item.description:
In order for electromagnetic (radio) waves to travel, a transmitting antenna and a receiving antenna are required. The path or mode in which the radio waves follow or can travel is termed as radio wave propagation.
There are three (3) modes of radio wave propagation is as follows;
Ground wave or surface wave propagation Space wave and line of sight (LOS) propagation Sky wave propagation Ground wave propagation Ground wave propagation is a mode of propagation in which the electromagnetic wave follows the curvature or contour of the earth.
